ANTHRAX, BOVINE - BENIN: (ATACORA)
**********************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[The location of the outbreak is in the commune of Boukoumbe in the region of Atacora in the northern part of the country near the border with Togo. In the original version of this post, the title line located the outbreak in Boukoumbe, in the below version we have corrected the location to mention the 1st administrative division - the region of Atacora. - Mod.MPP]

Date: 19 Mar 2012
Source: OIE [edited]
http://web.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=11775


OIE: Anthrax, Benin
-------------------
Information received on 19 Mar 2012 from Dr Richard Hounga Lokossou, Director, Ministry of Agriculture, Benin

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date: 16 Mar 2012
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 19 Mar 2012
Report date: 19 Mar 2012
Date submitted to OIE: 19 Mar 2012
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: February 2009
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Koutatahongou, Boukoumbe
Date of start of the outbreak: 16 Mar 2012
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 2 / 1 / 1 / 1 / 0
Affected Population: The disease was observed on an animal of a pair of draught oxen.

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak statistics
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 50.00 percent / 50.00 percent / 100.00 percent / 100.00 percent

* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: The outbreak was detected in an area of anthrax-infected fields. In February 2012, an outbreak occurred in Togo in the village of Kokou Tamberma on the northeastern border of Togo with Benin.

Control measures
Measures applied
* Quarantine
* Movement control inside the country
* Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s)
Administrative division / Species / Total Vaccinated / Details
Boukoumbe / Cattle / 2000 / - /
* No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied
* No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Laboratory of Natitingou (Local laboratory)
Tests and results
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / tissue imprints / 19 Mar 2012 / Positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations
Location of current outbreaks [Check site to see map.]

